description: The Universe Art Center is located in Ling-dong, Gwangjin-gu, Seoul. It is a global art center opened in 1981. It is a large theater with 1,082 seats and a comprehensive cultural space.

If you see a lot of young artists showcasing their work in Insadong, it's Ssamziegil. The pattern of this cultural space is very special, with a circular staircase in the central area from bottom to top. In each Kobo store, you can find a variety of products such as hanji crafts, ceramics, and fiber crafts.

place_name: SOMA - Seoul Olympic Museum of Art
description: The Soma Art Museum was formerly known as the Seoul Olympic Art Museum, which was established in 2004, and was renamed the SOMA Art Museum in 2006. The museum has two floors and consists of six exhibition halls. Among them, the Video Art Hall is a permanent exhibition room that displays the works of the late Korean video artist Mr. Paik Nam June. Others hold exhibitions from time to time. It should be noted that the SOMA Art Museum does not have an indoor toilet. There is an outdoor toilet on the right side of the art museum.

address: 26 Hwajung-ro, Deogyang-gu, Goyang-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea
